id: ResponsiveDesignPrinciples2025
description: >
  Enforces comprehensive UI/UX standards across visual design, interaction, accessibility, performance, and mobile-first responsiveness.
  This rule ensures all components adhere to brand guidelines, maintain usability across devices, and support consistent, accessible experiences.

scope:
  appliesTo: [all UI components, layouts, interactions, media, forms, navigation]
  alwaysApply: true
  conditionalOn: [tabs, functions, main design theme]

principles:
  VisualDesign:
    - Establish clear visual hierarchy
    - Use cohesive brand-aligned color palette (request user guidelines)
    - Apply effective typography for readability and emphasis
    - Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA contrast standards
    - Ensure consistent styling across application

  InteractionDesign:
    - Create intuitive navigation patterns
    - Use familiar UI components to reduce cognitive load
    - Provide clear calls-to-action
    - Implement responsive design for cross-device compatibility
    - Use animations judiciously

  Accessibility:
    - Follow WCAG guidelines
    - Use semantic HTML
    - Provide alt text for images and non-text content
    - Ensure keyboard navigability
    - Test with assistive technologies

  PerformanceOptimization:
    - Optimize images and assets
    - Implement lazy loading
    - Use code splitting
    - Monitor Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)

  UserFeedback:
    - Provide clear feedback for user actions
    - Use loading indicators
    - Offer clear error messages and recovery paths
    - Track user behavior via analytics

  InformationArchitecture:
    - Organize content logically
    - Use clear labeling and categorization
    - Implement search functionality
    - Create and maintain a sitemap

  MobileFirstDesign:
    - Design for mobile first
    - Use touch-friendly elements
    - Support gestures (swipe, pinch)
    - Prioritize thumb zones

  Consistency:
    - Adhere to a design system
    - Use consistent terminology and positioning
    - Maintain visual consistency across sections

  TestingAndIteration:
    - Conduct A/B testing
    - Use heatmaps and session recordings
    - Gather and apply user feedback
    - Iterate continuously

  Documentation:
    - Maintain style guide
    - Document design patterns and components
    - Create user flow diagrams
    - Organize design assets

  FluidLayouts:
    - Use relative units (%, em, rem)
    - Apply CSS Grid and Flexbox
    - Design mobile-first, scale up

  MediaQueries:
    - Use breakpoints for layout adjustment
    - Focus on content needs
    - Test across devices and orientations

  ImagesAndMedia:
    - Use responsive images (srcset, sizes)
    - Lazy load images and videos
    - Make embedded media responsive via CSS

  Typography:
    - Use em/rem for font sizes
    - Adjust line height and spacing for readability
    - Apply modular scale across breakpoints

  TouchTargets:
    - Minimum size: 44x44 pixels
    - Provide spacing between targets
    - Support hover and focus states

  Performance:
    - Optimize for mobile networks
    - Prefer CSS animations
    - Use critical CSS for above-the-fold content

  ContentPrioritization:
    - Prioritize mobile content
    - Use progressive disclosure
    - Apply off-canvas patterns for secondary content

  Navigation:
    - Use mobile-friendly patterns (e.g., hamburger menu)
    - Ensure keyboard and screen reader accessibility
    - Consider sticky headers

  Forms:
    - Responsive form layouts
    - Use mobile-friendly input types
    - Provide inline validation and clear errors

  Testing:
    - Use browser dev tools
    - Test on real devices
    - Conduct usability testing across device types

notes:
  - Stay updated with latest responsive design techniques and browser capabilities
  - Refer to industry-standard guidelines and evolving UI/UX best practices